excerpt: 11th century clifftop castle overlooking Lake Bled with a museum, restaurant & wine cellar.
detail_description: Bled Castle, a clifftop fortress dating back to the 11th century, stands proudly overlooking Lake Bled. Originally built in 1004 by Emperor Henry II, it was later inhabited by the Bishops of Brixen for over eight centuries. The castle has undergone renovations and expansions throughout the Middle Ages, including the addition of a chapel and other structures. Visitors can explore its museum and partake in various activities tied to the castle's history for an entrance fee.
name: Bled Castle

excerpt: Scenic lake surrounded by mountains & forest, featuring an island housing a historic church.
detail_description: Lake Bled is a picturesque destination, surrounded by mountains and forests, with a charming island that houses a historic church. The high season runs from May to October, attracting tourists from various countries. The local cuisine offers modern and diverse dishes, including homemade pasta, soups, and smoked trout specialties. Visitors can enjoy tasting menus featuring light and fresh dishes made from natural ingredients.
name: Lake Bled

excerpt: Landmark island with 99 steps to a 15th-century pilgrimage church & a cliffside medieval castle.
detail_description: Bled Island is a significant landmark featuring a 15th-century pilgrimage church and a medieval castle perched on a cliff. For an aerial view of the island and the church, visitors can hike to Ojstrica Hill or other higher locations for more privacy. The island is also known as one of the most romantic places in the world to propose, offering stunning sunset views above the lake.
name: Bled Island

excerpt: Bled, a Slovenian resort town in the foothills of the Julian Alps, is set along the glacial Lake Bled. On a cliff overlooking the lake is the 11th-century Bled Castle, which houses a museum, chapel and printing press. Atop a small island in the lake's center is the Pilgrimage Church of the Assumption of Maria, with its steep staircase and bell tower.
detail_description: Bled is a charming resort town nestled in the Julian Alps of Slovenia, boasting the picturesque Lake Bled. The iconic 11th-century Bled Castle overlooks the lake and houses a museum, chapel, and printing press. A must-see is the Pilgrimage Church of the Assumption of Maria situated on a small island in the center of the lake, featuring a striking bell tower and steep staircase. Visitors can indulge in exquisite dining experiences at various establishments within Bled.
name: Bled

excerpt: Hilltop viewpoint, reached by a steep, challenging hike, offering iconic panoramas of Lake Bled.
detail_description: Mala Osojnica is a hilltop viewpoint that offers breathtaking panoramic views of Lake Bled and its surroundings. Situated at an elevation of 670 meters, reaching this viewpoint involves a steep and challenging hike, but the effort is rewarded with iconic vistas. From this vantage point, visitors can enjoy a broad perspective of the lake with the mountains in the background, including notable landmarks such as Bled Island, Bled Castle, Mt. Stol, and Vrtaca.
name: Mala Osojnica

excerpt: Historic church located in a calm, picturesque setting on an island accessible by boat.
detail_description: The Church of the Assumption of the Blessed Virgin Mary is a historic and picturesque church located on a tiny island in Lake Bled, Slovenia. Accessible by boat, this charming church stands on the site of an eighth-century Slavic pagan temple and is a popular spot for weddings. Tradition dictates that grooms carry their brides up the 99 steps leading to the church door, adding to its romantic allure.
name: Church of the Assumption of the Blessed Virgin Mary

excerpt: Hilly park with lake & mountain views, plus adventure trails, zip lines & summer toboggan runs.
detail_description: Straza Hill above Lake Bled is a picturesque hilly park offering stunning views of the lake and surrounding mountains. It features adventure trails, zip lines, and summer toboggan runs for outdoor enthusiasts. The hill provides a scenic hike through the forest, culminating in breathtaking vistas of Lake Bled and the Julian Alps from its summit. Visitors can also enjoy a chairlift ride with beautiful nature views and an exciting rope course at the top.
name: Straza hill above Lake Bled

excerpt: This mountain in the Kamnik–Savinja Alps with a sharp, pyramid-shaped top features climbing routes.
detail_description: Ojstrica, a mountain in the Kamnik–Savinja Alps, boasts a distinctive pyramid-shaped peak and offers climbing routes. Hiking to Ojstrica Hill provides a breathtaking bird's eye view of Lake Bled and its iconic church on Bled Island. For a more secluded experience, there are two other popular locations further up the hill. Visitors are encouraged to embark on an early morning hike to witness the sunrise reflecting off the lake from this vantage point.
name: Ojstrica

detail_description: The Pletna Boat Cruise to the Island Bled offers a unique experience to visit the Church of the Assumption and explore the Bled Island Gallery. You can choose between traditional rowboats or larger Pletna boats for your journey. The island is known for its picturesque views and art inspired by its beauty, making it a must-visit destination for travelers seeking a new perspective.
name: PLETNA BOAT CRUISE TO THE ISLAND BLED

detail_description: St. Martin's Parish Church is a picturesque neo-Gothic church located on the edge of an alpine lake, overlooking the water between the castle and the town. Its spire, built in the early 1900s, is a prominent feature of Bled's skyline. Visitors can enjoy stunning views of the church from various vantage points around the lake and castle. The interior boasts magnificent artwork and frescoes that are truly breathtaking. Nearby, at Zima Cafe near St.
name: St. Martin Parish Church

excerpt: Small resort with lake & mountain views, popular for summer tobogganing & winter downhill skiing.
detail_description: Straža Bled is a small resort hill that offers stunning views of Lake Bled, the castle, and the surrounding mountains. It is a popular spot for both summer and winter activities. In the summer, visitors can enjoy adrenaline-pumping sledding on the slope with a gondola ride to the top and then a thrilling ride back down. There's also an Adventure Park and other attractions like tube rides and free fall simulators.
name: Straža Bled

detail_description: Café Belvedere, located in Bled, Slovenia, offers a historical and picturesque setting with its terrace designed by Slovene architect Joze Plecnik. Originally a waiting hall for audiences with King Alexander of Yugoslavia, it now serves as a charming spot to savor the famous local kremna rezina (cream cake) and enjoy cooked breakfasts on the terrace or indulge in a buffet featuring local meats and cheese indoors.
name: Café Belvedere

detail_description: Perched on a rocky outcrop 130 meters above Lake Bled in Slovenia, Bled Castle Restaurant is situated within the oldest medieval castle in the country. Offering panoramic views of the lake, iconic church on a small island, and the Karawank Mountains, this restaurant provides an unforgettable dining experience. The venue serves delectable local dishes and wines while allowing guests to enjoy breathtaking vistas of the surrounding landscape.
name: Bled Castle Restaurant

detail_description: Nestled on the western edge of Lake Bled, Velika Zaka is a delightful beach that beckons visitors with its refreshing waters and stunning surroundings. This free-access beach is conveniently located near the Velika Zaka parking lot, making it easy to reach. With public bathrooms nearby and an array of restaurants and gelato stands just a stone's throw away, it's perfect for a day of relaxation.
name: Velika Zaka

detail_description: Javni zavod Triglavski narodni park, or Triglav National Park Headquarters, is named after Slovenia's highest peak and covers most of the Julian Alps. This vast protected area is a natural wonderland boasting diverse landscapes with mountains, gorges, villages, water sources, and lush vegetation. The park is meticulously maintained and offers a wealth of natural beauty to explore.
name: Triglav National Park Headquarters

detail_description: Zipline Dolinka Bled offers an exhilarating adventure over the protected valley of Sava Dolinka, just a short distance from Lake Bled. With seven cables providing a unique outdoor experience, visitors can immerse themselves in nature, guided by knowledgeable locals who share the valley's story. The zipline park features a 4 km long zipline offering stunning views of the Julian Alps and Sava Dolinka River.
name: Zipline Dolinka Bled

detail_description: Velika Osojnica is a popular viewpoint in Bled, Slovenia, offering stunning panoramic views of Lake Bled and the surrounding mountains. The hike to Velika Osojnica involves a steep forty-five minute walk to Mala Osojnica followed by a short climb to the summit. From there, visitors can enjoy breathtaking vistas of the lake and its picturesque surroundings, including the Karavanke Mountains, the Kamnik-Savinja Alps, and the Goreniska Plain.
name: Velika Osojnica

detail_description: Bled Jezero railway station is a convenient option for travelers due to its proximity to accommodations and the lake. While there are limited trains from Ljubljana, the station's building is elegant and well-maintained. Travelers can check train schedules on the Slovenske Zeleznice website, but it's recommended to bring cash for tickets as online booking may not be reliable. The station offers a peaceful atmosphere with beautiful mountain views, making it a pleasant stop for visitors.
name: Bled Jezero

detail_description: Provost's House in Bled, Slovenia is a historical landmark located on Bled Island. Once a private residence, it has been transformed into a museum, gallery, and souvenir shop. Visitors can reach the island by boat and explore the house while enjoying magnificent views of the surrounding area. The Provost's House offers superb photo opportunities and is particularly beautiful during autumn with its colorful foliage.
name: Provost's House

detail_description: Mlino is a charming village located on the shores of Lake Bled in Slovenia. It is known for its traditional architecture, including beautiful wooden houses and a picturesque church. Visitors can explore the local culture at the village museum and enjoy stunning views of the lake and surrounding mountains. Mlino offers a peaceful and idyllic setting for those looking to experience the natural beauty and rich heritage of this region.
name: Mlino

detail_description: Nestled by the lakeside in Bled, Oštarija Peglez'n is a charming restaurant that exudes a cozy and nostalgic ambiance. The interior is adorned with an eclectic mix of rustic trinkets, creating a homely atmosphere reminiscent of a beloved Slovenian grandmother's abode. Dating back to the 16th century as a blacksmith's workshop, this establishment has retained its historical charm with exposed wooden beams and stone walls.
name: Oštarija Peglez'n

excerpt: Outdoor adventure park offering zip lines, climbing tracks & other challenges for children & adults.
detail_description: Pustolovski park Bled is a popular outdoor adventure park in Straza Park, offering a variety of challenges for both children and adults. It provides obstacle courses with zip lining and stunning views of Bled Castle. The park is well-equipped with facilities and offers a great experience for families. Visitors can enjoy the natural surroundings and kind instructors while engaging in activities suitable for kids of all ages. However, it's advisable to bring your own food as there are limited dining options at the park.
name: Pustolovski park Bled

detail_description: The tourist information center Mamut Slovenia is a great place to find out about the surrounding areas and learn about all the available activities. They offer day trips, outdoor activities, transfers and even bikes. This is the perfect way to get started exploring this beautiful country!
name: Mamut Slovenia - Tourist agency in Bled offering Day Trips, Outdoor Activities, Transfers, Bikes

detail_description: Tourist farm Dolinar Krainer is located in the peaceful village of Kupljenik, surrounded by wildflower meadows and traditional Slovenian hayracks. Just a 10-minute drive from Lake Bled, it offers a tranquil escape while still being close to the town's attractions. The hosts, Iza and her husband, warmly welcome guests and provide valuable tips for exploring the area. The farm's homemade breakfast is highly recommended, featuring delicious products straight from the farm.
name: Tourist farm Dolinar Krainer

detail_description: Old Cellar Bled is a charming restaurant located in downtown Bled, offering a cozy and romantic atmosphere. The establishment prides itself on sourcing local products from Slovenia and boasts an impressive wine list. Visitors can indulge in classic Slovenian dishes and traditional desserts while enjoying the extensive selection of Slovenian wines. With its 500-year-old cellar, Old Cellar Bled provides great service and a delightful culinary experience that combines tradition with innovation.
name: Old Cellar Bled (Lake view)

excerpt: Casual, old-fashioned eatery with a global menu featuring plant-based meals & desserts, plus juices.
detail_description: Public & Vegan Kitchen Bled is a cozy and laid-back restaurant with a diverse menu that includes plant-based dishes, desserts, and refreshing juices. Situated in an old-fashioned setting reminiscent of an Irish pub, this eatery offers a global selection of vegan meals. It's the only vegan restaurant in Bled and has been serving its patrons since before another similar establishment moved to Ljubljana.
name: Public & Vegan Kitchen Bled

detail_description: Pizzeria Rustika, located in Lake Bled, has been hailed as the top spot for pizza by Tripadvisor. The restaurant offers a warm and cozy ambiance, making it an ideal place to unwind after a day of outdoor adventures. Their extensive menu features a variety of mouthwatering options cooked to perfection in their large pizza oven. Whether you prefer the classic margherita or more adventurous toppings, Pizzeria Rustika guarantees high-quality and flavorful pizzas.
name: Pizzeria Rustika

excerpt: Wooden deck over lake waters, with Bled Castle views & a heart-shaped frame popular for photos.
detail_description: "The Heart of Bled" is a picturesque wooden deck overlooking the lake, offering stunning views of Bled Castle and featuring a heart-shaped frame that's popular for photos. Designed by gardeners Matevz and Joza Cop, it was influenced by Swedish landscaper Swenson. The area around Vila Pongratz used to be a cultural center with a music pavilion, tennis courts, and sweet stalls.
name: The Heart of Bled

detail_description: Hotel Starkl is a charming family-run property situated on the shores of Bled Lake, offering unique and picturesque views. The hotel provides comfortable rooms with modern amenities such as flat-screen TVs and free Wi-Fi. Guests can enjoy delicious meals at the on-site restaurant and unwind at the bar with a terrace. Additionally, the hotel offers recreational activities like bicycle rentals and tour assistance.
name: Hotel Starkl

detail_description: Rent a Sup/boat Vila Bled offers the perfect opportunity to explore the serene waters of Lake Bled. With its wooden boats available for rental, visitors can enjoy a peaceful rowing experience on the calm lake, making it suitable for beginners as well. The property provides convenient boat rental services to visit Lake Bled and Bled Island, allowing guests to take in the breathtaking scenery at their own pace.
name: Rent a Sup/boat Vila Bled

detail_description: Potičnica is a charming souvenir shop located on Bled Island, offering a delightful experience for visitors. The shop provides an opportunity to savor the renowned potica cake and indulge in delicious coffee and tea. Additionally, it boasts a variety of ice cream flavors, including unique options like apple pie and Bled cream cake. Visitors can enjoy their treats while taking in the stunning views outside or relaxing under the shades.
name: Potičnica

excerpt: Unfussy rooms in a casual hotel offering a bar & free Wi-Fi, plus event space & bike rentals.
detail_description: This hotel is situated in the town of Bled, next to the Church of Saint Martin. The accommodation comprises of unfussy rooms with a shared bathroom. There is also a bar and free Wi-Fi access. The property also has event space and bike rentals available for guests.
name: Old Parish House

detail_description: Restavracija Central Bled is a charming eatery that offers authentic Slovenian cuisine. The menu features traditional dishes like kranjska klobasa, struklji, and golaz. While the restaurant can get busy during peak tourist season, the service is efficient although it may feel somewhat transactional. Some patrons found the food to be satisfactory, with highlights including Slovenian cottage cheese dumplings and Bled cream cake.
name: Restavracija Central Bled

detail_description: As you arrive at the picturesque lake, take a leisurely stroll along the lakeside promenade known as Cesta svobode. This charming pathway invites you to meander around the shimmering waters, offering stunning views and a serene atmosphere. Keep walking until you reach the end of this delightful promenade, where you'll discover an inviting path that ascends to your right, beckoning you to explore further into nature's embrace.
name: Cesta svobode

detail_description: Dobra Gora is a charming and picturesque destination nestled in the heart of the countryside. Visitors can expect stunning natural scenery, including lush greenery and rolling hills. The area is known for its peaceful atmosphere, making it an ideal retreat for those looking to escape the hustle and bustle of city life. Dobra Gora offers a variety of outdoor activities such as hiking, cycling, and birdwatching, allowing nature enthusiasts to fully immerse themselves in the tranquil surroundings.
name: Dobra Gora

detail_description: Sunrise View Straza offers a breathtaking spectacle as the morning light paints the sky over Lake Bled and the Julian Alps. The best vantage point for this stunning sunrise is from Mala Osjinica, a popular hiking spot in Bled. Visitors can enjoy amazing views of the mountain ridges while witnessing this natural wonder unfold before their eyes.
name: Sunrise View Straza

detail_description: IdealRENT Rent a Car & Chauffeur Service is highly recommended for those looking to rent a car in Slovenia. The agency offers excellent service and flexibility, allowing travelers to explore the wonders surrounding the lake at their own pace. Customers have praised Mr. Dejan for his exceptional assistance in arranging car rentals, ensuring a smooth and enjoyable holiday experience.
name: idealRENT Rent a Car & Chauffeur Service

detail_description: Dolinka River Lounge offers an exhilarating ziplining experience over the scenic Dolinka River near Bled. Visitors can enjoy a thrilling adventure while taking in breathtaking views of the surrounding natural beauty. Additionally, guests can indulge in delectable dining options, including mouthwatering pizzas, refreshing beer, and delightful desserts at reasonable prices. The friendly and attentive staff further enhance the overall experience, making it a must-visit destination for both adventure seekers and food enthusiasts alike.
name: Dolinka River Lounge
address: River Camping Bled, Alpska cesta 111, 4248 Lesce, Slovenia

detail_description: Apartment Galerija Bled is a well-appointed accommodation that can accommodate up to 4 adults, featuring a terrace with stunning mountain views and private parking. Situated within walking distance of the lake, it offers a comfortable living space and a convenient location. Guests have praised the cleanliness of the apartment and its amenities, including a comfortable sofa bed. While some found its location slightly removed from Bled Town Center, others appreciated its proximity to essential services and beautiful surroundings.
name: Apartment Galerija Bled

excerpt: Sprawling biosphere reserve named after the mountain it includes, the 2,864m-high Triglav.
detail_description: Triglav National Park is a vast biosphere reserve named after the 2,864m-high Triglav mountain. The park offers a range of outdoor activities and sightseeing opportunities, from hiking and climbing to exploring emerald waters and majestic peaks. Visitors can explore Lake Bled, surrounded by lush forests and overlooked by a medieval castle, as well as take in the stunning views of the park's imposing cliffs and Russian chapel.
name: Triglav National Park

detail_description: At the edge of a picturesque lake, Čolnar stands as a statue overlooking the serene waters. Visitors can enjoy swimming in the lake while taking in the beautiful surroundings. The area is known for its pleasant weather and occasional waves created by the southern wind, adding to the charm of this tranquil spot.
name: Čolnar

detail_description: Čebelarstvo Ambrožič - Kralov Med offers an educational guided tour that provides a thorough and informative experience. Visitors have the opportunity to learn about beekeeping, observe the bees up close, and gain valuable insights into the process. The passionate hosts ensure an engaging and memorable visit, with opportunities to taste delicious honey and explore a well-priced gift shop.
name: Čebelarstvo Ambrožič - Kralov Med

detail_description: Slap Iglica, perched above the charming village of Bohinjska Bela, is far from your typical lookout point. This stunning location features impressive rocky walls that attract climbers and adventurers alike. The Suha stream meanders through these cliffs, culminating in a breathtaking 24-meter waterfall that cascades dramatically over a vertical drop. While the waterfall itself may not be the main attraction, the panoramic views it offers are simply spectacular.
name: Slap Iglica

detail_description: The Amazing Animals museum in Slovenia offers a unique and unexpected exhibition of lizards and snakes. Each creature has its own tale, with some being rescued from certain death, others donated, and some simply unwanted by their previous owners. By visiting this exhibition, you indirectly support these animals by contributing towards their food expenses. It is highly recommended due to the vast variety of snakes, lizards, spiders, and more that it showcases.
name: Amazing Animals

excerpt: Marked hiking trails wind along grassy ridges to a summit with views of neighboring mountains.
detail_description: Viševnik is a popular hiking destination located west of Pokljuka plateau. The conically shaped summit, standing at 2050 meters high, offers stunning views of neighboring mountains. Accessible from Rudno Polje, the trail leads hikers along grassy ridges to the narrow peak. The ascent can be steep and challenging, especially in wet conditions or during winter. Hikers can choose from two trails to reach the summit and make a loop to avoid retracing their steps.
name: Viševnik
